         <div type="entry">
                <head>Abrohom Naḥshirtono</head>
                <ab type="idnos">
                    <idno type="URI">https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Abrohom-Nahshirtono</idno>
                    <idno type="syriaca-bibl">http://syriaca.org/bibl/27</idno>
                    <idno type="entry">18</idno>
                    <milestone unit="pages" n="9"/>
                    <idno type="subject">http://syriaca.org/person/110</idno>
                    <note type="type">person</note>
                    <note type="abstract">Maphrian of the East and author of an Anaphora.<note/>
                    </note>
                </ab>
                <ab type="infobox">(d. 686) [<abbr>Syr. Orth.</abbr>]</ab>
                <div type="body">
                    <p>
                        <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Maphrian">Maphrian</ref> of the East and author of an Anaphora. He was nicknamed
                            <hi rend="italic">naḥširtono</hi> (Ar. <hi rend="italic">al-ṣayyād</hi>)
                        ‘the hunter’. He was consecrated as Maphrian by <ref rend="bold"
                       target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Athanasios-II-of-Balad">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/109">Athanasios
                            II of Balad</persName>
                        </ref>.</p>
                </div>
                <div type="bibl">
                    <head>Sources</head>
                    <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Barsoum, <title rend="italic">Scattered pearls</title>,
                            333.</bibl>
                        <bibl>A. Konat, <title rend="italic">Ktobo d-ṭekso d-Annafura</title>
                            (1986), 250–60.</bibl>
                        <bibl>I. Saka, <title rend="italic">Kanīsatī al-suryāniyya</title> (1985),
                            216.</bibl>
                    </listBibl>
                </div>
